entries.title: What to expect from Biden's State of the Union address
Previously unknown layer of molten rock found beneath Earth's crust
entries.description: Researchers have detected a previously unknown layer of partially molten rock beneath Earth's crust.

entries.title: Before and after satellite images show destruction in Turkey
entries.description: Collapsed buildings, emergency vehicles and tent shelters can be seen in new satellite imagery of earthquake-hit towns in Turkey, revealing the damage from Monday's devastating earthquake.

entries.title: Hear George Santos respond to constituents calling for his resignation
entries.description: A group of constituents from Rep. George Santos' New York district traveled to Capitol Hill calling for his resignation. Hear the freshman congressman's response.

entries.title: Hopes wither amid bitter cold as rescuers race to find survivors
entries.description: Standing in front of the flattened remains of a 10-story building in the Turkish city of Gaziantep, a man anxiously waits for news about his friend Mustafa, who is trapped beneath the rubble.

entries.title: Meet the innocent looking cat that upended the chess world
entries.description: This harmless looking cat-themed chess bot called "Mittens" has a single digit Elo score, but it has bewildered the world of chess while evolving into an internet meme.

entries.title: Avlon: These are the key things Biden needs to address in State of the Union
entries.description: CNN senior political analyst John Avlon and CNN political commentator Margaret Hoover discuss President Joe Biden's State of the Union address, including what he will need to convey to the American people.

entries.title: Alec Baldwin's legal team moves to disqualify special prosecutor overseeing 'Rust' case
entries.description: An attorney for actor Alec Baldwin filed a motion Tuesday to disqualify special prosecutor Andrea Reeb, who is overseeing the "Rust" shooting case.

entries.title: China has more ICBM launchers than US, senior general tells lawmakers
entries.description: A senior American military officer notified lawmakers in January that China has more land-based fixed and mobile intercontinental ballistic missile launchers than the US, according to a letter sent to Congress.

entries.title: Newborn baby reportedly rescued from earthquake rubble in Syria
entries.description: A baby girl has been reportedly rescued from the rubble of her home in northern Syria following Monday's massive earthquake.

entries.title: Officers charged over Tyre Nichols' death allegedly assaulted another man 3 days before
entries.description: Five Memphis police officers charged in the deadly police beating of Tyre Nichols last month are accused of assaulting another young Black man just three days prior, according to a federal lawsuit filed Tuesday.

entries.title: 4 people hospitalized after battery fire in United plane cabin
entries.description: A fire from the battery of an electrical device aboard a United Airlines flight forced a Newark-bound plane to return to San Diego on Tuesday and sent four people to the hospital, officials say.

entries.title: Could zombie fungi take over humans? Dr. Gupta explains
entries.description: Dr. Sanjay Gupta explains whether or not zombie fungi, like the ones depicted in HBO's popular series "The Last of Us," can take over humanity.

entries.title: Aid worker: Some Syrian towns 'completely wiped out'
entries.description: Christiane Amanpour speaks with Sherine Ibrahim, Country Director for CARE Türkiye, on the race to reach more survivors under the rubble caused by the massive earthquake in Turkey and Syria.

entries.title: Watch Alison Brie freestyle rap the plot to her new movie
entries.description: Alison Brie stole the spotlight on "The Tonight Show" when she turned the plot of her latest movie "Somebody I Used to Know" into a freestyle rap. Brie co-wrote The Amazon Prime film with her husband and director Dave Franco.

entries.title: Map: Aftershocks felt across the region after major earthquake hits Turkey
McCarthy confirms George Santos is facing US House probe
entries.description: House Speaker Kevin McCarthy said New York GOP Rep. George Santos is facing a House Ethics Committee probe, confirming for the first time that the panel has opened an investigation into the embattled freshman. McCarthy said the House will take action depending on what the panel finds.

entries.title: Explainer: The earthquake in Turkey is one of the deadliest this century. Here's why
entries.description: More than 5,000 people were killed and tens of thousands more injured in Turkey and Syria after Monday's devastating earthquake.

entries.title: Harry Styles and dancers surprised by turntable spinning the wrong way during Grammys performance
entries.description: If Harry Styles and his backup dancers looked a little out of it during their performance at Sunday's Grammys, there's good reason.

entries.title: Kevin Costner leaving 'Yellowstone?' Paramount responds
entries.description: Speculation that Kevin Costner may be leaving the hit drama "Yellowstone" has reached such a fevered pitch that Paramount has responded.

entries.title: UNESCO site 'in danger' faces greater peril after earthquake
entries.description: The devastating earthquakes in Turkey and Syria on Monday have damaged important historic sites, including the ancient city of Aleppo in northwest Syria which was already "in danger" from civil war.

entries.title: Tennis star Jessica Pegula says her sister saved her mom's life during cardiac arrest in 2022
entries.description: US tennis star Jessica Pegula says her sister, Kelly, saved their mom's life after she went into cardiac arrest at her home last year.

entries.title: Chris Brown apologizes to Robert Glasper after upset over Grammy loss
entries.description: Chris Brown is apologizing for an online outburst after he lost the Grammy for best R&B album to pianist Robert Glasper.

entries.title: US senators seek answers from Meta on whether user data was accessed by China, Russia and others
entries.description: Top US lawmakers on the Senate Intelligence Committee want answers from Meta on a newly disclosed internal investigation it conducted in 2018 that found tens of thousands of software developers in China, Russia and other "high-risk" countries may have had access to detailed Facebook user data before the company clamped down on that access beginning in 2014.

entries.title: 'Hogwarts Legacy' game appears to introduce 'Harry Potter's' first trans character
entries.description: A hotly anticipated new video game set in the "Harry Potter" universe appears to feature a trans character, which would be a first for the franchise.

entries.title: Mady Gosselin slams comments about her 'Jon & Kate Plus 8' family
entries.description: Mady Gosselin is tired of the public feeling like they are owed access to her family members because they were once reality stars.

entries.title: This Fed official grocery shops for his family and knows just how high prices are
entries.description: Neel Kashkari, president of the Federal Reserve Bank of Minneapolis, understands that consumers are still struggling to deal with high prices. And he has the frozen lasagna to prove it.

entries.title: After the Super Bowl, State Farm stadium will have tons of leftovers. Here's how  that food will get to to people in need fast
entries.description: On Super Bowl Sunday, an army of volunteers will be ready outside and inside State Farm Stadium in Glendale, Arizona to execute a time-sensitive game plan of their own. Their mission: recover and redistribute a tremendous volume of surplus food.

entries.title: Researchers: 15 million people at risk from catastrophic glacial lake outbursts
entries.description: Glaciers around the world are melting at an alarming rate, and are leaving massive pools of water in their wake. The meltwater fills the depression left behind by the glacier, forming what's known as a glacial lake.

entries.title: Opinion: Why Netanyahu is suddenly a lot less friendly with Putin
entries.description: Long before the current war in Ukraine began nearly a year ago, Israel has maintained strict neutrality in the hostilities between Russia and Ukraine. That may be about to change.

entries.title: CNN reports from scene of rescue operation in Turkey
entries.description: CNN's Becky Anderson reports from Gaziantep, Turkey after a powerful 7.8 magnitude earthquake rocked the region killing thousands and injuring thousands more.

entries.title: Memphis City Council to take up reform proposals at first hearing since release of Tyre Nichols video
entries.description: The Memphis City Council is set to discuss nearly a dozen public safety proposals and departmental reforms with the police chief and fire chief on Tuesday morning at the council's first public hearing since the release of disturbing video showing the police beating of Tyre Nichols.

entries.title: 'Britcoin' could arrive in the second half of the decade
entries.description: The United Kingdom is pushing ahead with plans to create a digital pound issued by the Bank of England that would offer a stable alternative to bitcoin or ether.

entries.title: 'Bill Russell: Legend' plays a complete game in celebrating basketball's greatest winner
entries.description: Bill Russell is often shortchanged by those lists of the greatest NBA players, so leave it to fellow all-stars of his era Bill Bradley ("The smartest player that ever played the game") and Jerry West ("We're never going to see a winner like that again") to appropriately eulogize him in "Bill: Russell Legend," a two-part Netflix documentary that covers the Boston Celtics great's triumphs on the court, and activism off of it.

entries.title: Climate change is contributing to the rise of superbugs, new UN report says
entries.description: Climate change and antimicrobial resistance are two of the greatest threats to global health, according to a new report from the United Nations Environment Programme.

entries.title: Boeing is cutting 2,000 HR and finance jobs, outsourcing some to India
entries.description: Boeing plans to cut about 2,000 white-collar jobs in finance and human resources, and it will be shifting some of that work to an outside contractor in India.

entries.title: Eminem's daughter Hailie Jade gets engaged
entries.description: Eminem's daughter is getting a new last name.

entries.title: The Grammys prove that LGBTQ artists are no longer on the sidelines
entries.description: The 65th annual Grammy Awards brought some needed joy to our current cultural climate. Happiness was at full tilt — from the celebration of 50 years of hip-hop to emotional speeches from Lizzo and others to Beyoncé making history as the most-decorated Grammy-winning musician.

entries.title: Surfer Bethany Hamilton says she won't compete in WSL events if new transgender rules are upheld
entries.description: Surfer Bethany Hamilton says she won't compete at future World Surf League (WSL) events if it upholds its new policy on transgender athletes, saying she wants to see a different division created for transgender people to compete in.

entries.title: Be explicit about talking to your partner about sex, say this couple
entries.description: The timeless advice for couples about the importance of communicating when it comes to sex might be as old as the act itself.

entries.title: Amazon to donate supplies to Turkey's earthquake victims
entries.description: Amazon has announced that it will help victims of the Turkey earthquake by donating food, medicine and equipment from its Istanbul warehouse.

entries.title: 'Speed is of the essence': How Europe is helping Turkey
entries.description: European Commissioner for Crisis Management Janez Lenarcic talks to Christiane Amanpour about the massive earthquake that struck Syria and Turkey.

entries.title: LeBron James says he is 'definitely disappointed' Los Angeles Lakers couldn't acquire Kyrie Irving
entries.description: LeBron James admits he is "definitely disappointed" that the Los Angeles Lakers were unable to acquire Kyrie Irving in a trade, with the former Brooklyn Nets guard instead being dealt to the Dallas Mavericks on Sunday.

entries.title: Whale tangled in fishing gear and lobster pots freed by rescuers
entries.description: A North Atlantic right whale was left in a dire situation after it became entangled in commercial fishing rope and lobster pots.

entries.title: The fungal threat to human health is growing in a warmer, wetter, sicker world
entries.description: In the HBO show "The Last of Us," characters identify zombies among them by the fungi that bursts from their bodies, and fungal parasites manipulate the humans to infect the communities around them.

entries.title: Ghanaian footballer Christian Atsu found alive in Turkey earthquake rubble
entries.description: International football player Christian Atsu has been found alive following Monday's earthquake in southern Turkey, Ghana Football Association said on Tuesday.

entries.title: How to watch President Joe Biden's State of the Union address
From mouth purses to blinking eye dice, this artist creates flesh-like accessories
entries.description: Inspired by his love of horror films, Japanese DJ and artist Masataka Shishido talks to Reuters about creating freaky flesh-like accessories ranging from mouth-shaped purses to dice with blinking eyes controlled by a remote.

entries.title: Federal lawsuit filed over Kenosha police officer who put his knee on a 12-year-old's neck while breaking up school fight
entries.description: A father and his middle-school-aged daughter have filed a federal lawsuit against a former school security guard in Kenosha, Wisconsin, after he put his knee on the child's neck while trying to break up a cafeteria fight last year.

entries.title: She got the last seat on a flight next to a stranger. They've been married for 40 years
entries.description: Vickie Moretz had never left the southern United States, let alone traveled abroad. The prospect of flying across the Atlantic was equal parts exhilarating and terrifying.

entries.title: Opinion: What Peter Thiel and the 'Pudding Guy' revealed
entries.description: The Roth IRA is a retirement account allowed by a 1997 law. It's intended for middle-​class investors and has limits on both the investor's income level and the amount that can be invested.

entries.title: How the first Black woman to help discover an element 'claimed a seat at the periodic table'
entries.description: As a kid, Clarice Phelps often turned to one image for inspiration.

entries.title: Drone footage: See the scale of damage from the sky
entries.description: Thousands of buildings have collapsed in Turkey and Syria, where a 7.8 magnitude earthquake killed at least 5,000 people on Monday.

entries.title: 'Crisis in a crisis': Syrians are already devastated by civil war
entries.description: For many of the Syrian victims of the devastating earthquake that hit Turkey and Syria on Monday, this is just the latest in a decade-long series of tragedies.

entries.title: George Santos' saga casts a spotlight on his longtime campaign treasurer -- and her other clients
entries.description: In the fall of 2020, then-New York Rep. Lee Zeldin's campaign submitted a report to federal regulators with a series of unusual expenses: 21 payments on a single day of exactly $199.99 each. The outlays -- each just one penny below the dollar figure above which campaigns are required to keep receipts -- all went to anonymous recipients.

entries.title: Jill Biden's State of the Union guests include Tyre Nichols' parents, Bono, Ukraine ambassador, Paul Pelosi
entries.description: Paul Pelosi, Tyre Nichols' parents, U2 star Bono, Monterey Park shooting hero Brandon Tsay, Ukraine's ambassador to the US Oksana Markarova and a Holocaust survivor are among those headed to the US Capitol Tuesday evening where President Joe Biden is set to deliver his State of the Union address.

entries.title: Ukrainian official claims Russia plans to mobilize up to half a million extra soldiers
Survivors are still being pulled from the rubble more than 24 hours after Turkey earthquake
entries.description: Survivors are still being pulled from the rubble in Turkey and Syria, more than 24 hours after a powerful earthquake toppled thousands of homes, killing nearly 4,900 people.

entries.title: BP's annual profit more than doubles to $28 billion
entries.description: BP's annual profit more than doubled last year to nearly $28 billion, extending a record run of earnings for the world's oil majors that is adding to calls for higher taxes on the windfall gains.

entries.description: • Why CNN will be reporting about gender inequalities online

entries.title: Louisiana State Police are investigating the deadly shooting of an unarmed Black man by an officer
entries.description: Authorities in Louisiana are investigating the deadly shooting of an unarmed Black man by an officer, state police said in a statement.

entries.title: Prospects for peace in Ukraine are diminishing as world faces a wider war: UN chief
How to help: The organizations involved in relief efforts
entries.description: Thousands of people are dead and many more are injured after a massive earthquake rocked Turkey and Syria Monday morning. The magnitude 7.8 quake was one of the strongest to strike the area in more than a century. Amid severe aftershocks, Turkey's Disaster and Emergency Management Agency (AFAD) called for international help.

entries.title: Turkey has sent a formal request to NATO and allies for assistance in dealing with the aftermath of the earthquake

The husband-and-wife forgers who fooled the art market — and made millions
entries.description: After decades of painting fakes, falsifying evidence and diligently covering their tracks, it was a single act of carelessness that brought the Beltracchis' deception to light.

entries.title: Australia's central bank signals more tightening ahead after hiking rates to decade high
entries.description: Australia's central bank raised its cash rate by 25 basis points to a decade-high of 3.35% on Tuesday and reiterated that further increases would be needed, in a more hawkish policy tilt than many had expected.

entries.title: 10 of the world's most sustainable ski resorts
entries.description: A great gulp of crisp mountain air and a gaze across pristine peaks is enough to remind you of the soul-stirring benefits of a ski holiday.

Microsoft Outlook email experiences outage
entries.description: Microsoft Outlook experienced an outage late Monday night and into Tuesday morning.

entries.title: Witness testifies conversation with Murdaugh on night of killings made her 'nervous'
entries.description: Key testimony from a witness in Alex Murdaugh's murder trial said she talked with Murdaugh on the night of his wife's and son's deaths, and that he made her 'nervous'. CNN's Randi Kaye reports.

entries.title: Chinese search engine giant Baidu announces ChatGPT-style AI bot
entries.description: Chinese search engine giant Baidu says it will be launching its own ChatGPT-style service.

entries.title: This 102-year-old Ukrainian survived Stalin's forced famine. Now she is making camouflage sniper suits
entries.description: Traditional Ukrainian tapestries, family photos and pastoral scenes on cheap posters cover the walls of her cottage warmed by a wood-burning stove. The only record of her tragic past are her birth certificate and her memories.

entries.title: Officials warn of 'grave danger of death' near burning, derailed train in Ohio
entries.description: A derailed train car carrying a hazardous chemical in the midst of a burning freight wreck may be on the brink of exploding -- and releasing toxic gas while hurling deadly shrapnel up to a mile away, officials on the eastern edge of Ohio said.

entries.title: More than 4,300 dead in Turkey and Syria after powerful quake
Putin's reputed girlfriend makes public comments about Ukraine war
entries.description: CNN's Erin Burnett discusses a new video showing Russian President Vladimir Putin's reputed girlfriend Alina Kabaeva liken war propaganda to a Kalashnikov.

entries.title: Saudi Arabia unveils face of ancient Nabataean woman
entries.description: Saudi Arabia is unveiling a reconstruction of the face of an ancient Nabataean woman after several years of work by historians and archaeologists.

entries.title: Jupiter now has the most moons in the solar system after new discovery
entries.description: Jupiter already reigns as king of the planets — it's the largest one in our solar system. And now, the gas giant has the most known moons, too.

entries.title: 'Total miscalculation': China goes into crisis management mode on balloon fallout
entries.description: • Exclusive: US intel assessment documents Chinese spy balloon incident under Trump

entries.title: Ted Cruz introduces 2-term limit bill. He's seeking a third term
entries.description: Sen. Ted Cruz introduced a bill to limit US senators to two terms while the Texas GOP senator is running for his third term in office. CNN's Jake Tapper and USA Today columnist Kirsten Powers react.

entries.title: Father weeps over body of infant son in emotional video
entries.description: CNN's Scott McLean shows harrowing video on the ground in Syria after a powerful magnitude 7.8 earthquake struck Turkey and Syria, leaving thousands of people killed or injured.
